#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.23:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Saraṇānivagga "
msgstr "3. About Sarakāni "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 23. Godhasakkasutta → tatiyamahānāmasuttaṃ (bj) | godhā or mahānāma 3 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Godhasakkasutta "
msgstr "23. With Godhā the Sakyan "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.372, sc1
msgctxt "sn55.23:1.1"
msgid "Kapilavatthunidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Kapilavatthu. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena godhā sakko tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā godhaṃ sakkaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Mahānāma the Sakyan went up to Godhā the Sakyan, and said to him, "

#. VAR: katihi → katīhi (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn55.23:1.3"
msgid "“katihi tvaṃ, godhe, dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāsi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇan”ti? "
msgstr "“Godhā, how many things must a person have for you to recognize them as a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn55.23:2.1"
msgid "“Tīhi khvāhaṃ, mahānāma, dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "“Mahānāma, a person must have three things for me to recognize them as a stream-enterer. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "sn55.23:2.3"
msgid "Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:2.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:2.5"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:2.6"
msgid "saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "and the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:2.7"
msgid "suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:2.8"
msgid "Imehi khvāhaṃ, mahānāma, tīhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "When a person has these three things I recognize them as a stream-enterer. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn55.23:3.1"
msgid "Tvaṃ pana, mahānāma, katihi dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāsi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇan”ti? "
msgstr "But Mahānāma, how many things must a person have for *you* to recognize them as a stream-enterer?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.23:3.2"
msgid "“Catūhi khvāhaṃ, godhe, dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "“Godhā, a person must have four things for me to recognize them as a stream-enterer. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:3.3"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn55.23:3.4"
msgid "Idha, godhe, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:3.5"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:3.6"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:3.7"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:3.8"
msgid "ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:3.9"
msgid "Imehi khvāhaṃ, godhe, catūhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇan”ti. "
msgstr "When a person has these four things I recognize them as a stream-enterer.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.373, sc4
msgctxt "sn55.23:4.1"
msgid "“Āgamehi tvaṃ, mahānāma, āgamehi tvaṃ, mahānāma. "
msgstr "“Hold on, Mahānāma, hold on! "

msgctxt "sn55.23:4.2"
msgid "Bhagavāva etaṃ jāneyya etehi dhammehi samannāgataṃ vā asamannāgataṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "Only the Buddha would know whether or not they have these things.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.23:4.3"
msgid "“Āyāma, godhe, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocessāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“Come, Godhā, let’s go to the Buddha and inform him about this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.23:4.4"
msgid "Atha kho mahānāmo sakko godhā ca sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Mahānāma and Godhā went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Mahānāma told the Buddha all that had happened, and then said: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn55.23:5.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, yena godhā sakko tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā godhaṃ sakkaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:5.2"
msgid "‘katihi tvaṃ, godhe, dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāsi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇaṃ’? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, godhā sakko maṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn55.23:6.1"
msgid "Tīhi khvāhaṃ, mahānāma, dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.3"
msgid "Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.5"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.6"
msgid "saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.7"
msgid "suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.8"
msgid "Imehi khvāhaṃ, mahānāma, tīhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:6.9"
msgid "Tvaṃ pana, mahānāma, katamehi dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāsi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇan’ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn55.23:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, bhante, godhaṃ sakkaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.2"
msgid "‘catūhi khvāhaṃ, godhe, dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.3"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.4"
msgid "Idha, godhe, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.5"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.6"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.7"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.8"
msgid "ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:7.9"
msgid "Imehi khvāhaṃ, godhe, catūhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ sotāpannapuggalaṃ ājānāmi avinipātadhammaṃ niyataṃ sambodhiparāyaṇan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.374, sc8
msgctxt "sn55.23:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, godhā sakko maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.2"
msgid "‘āgamehi tvaṃ, mahānāma, āgamehi tvaṃ, mahānāma. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.3"
msgid "Bhagavāva etaṃ jāneyya etehi dhammehi samannāgataṃ vā asamannāgataṃ vā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.4"
msgid "Idha, bhante, kocideva dhammo samuppādo uppajjeyya, ekato assa bhagavā ekato bhikkhusaṅgho ca. "
msgstr "“Sir, some issue regarding the teaching might come up. The Buddha might take one side, and the Saṅgha of monks the other. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.5"
msgid "Yeneva bhagavā tenevāhaṃ assaṃ. "
msgstr "I’d side with the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.6"
msgid "Evaṃ pasannaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu. "
msgstr "May the Buddha remember me as having such confidence. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.7"
msgid "Idha, bhante, kocideva dhammo samuppādo uppajjeyya, ekato assa bhagavā ekato bhikkhusaṅgho bhikkhunisaṅgho ca. "
msgstr "Some issue regarding the teaching might come up. The Buddha might take one side, and the Saṅgha of monks and the Saṅgha of nuns the other. … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.8"
msgid "Yeneva bhagavā tenevāhaṃ assaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.9"
msgid "Evaṃ pasannaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.10"
msgid "Idha, bhante, kocideva dhammo samuppādo uppajjeyya, ekato assa bhagavā ekato bhikkhusaṅgho bhikkhunisaṅgho ca upāsakā ca. "
msgstr "The Buddha might take one side, and the Saṅgha of monks and the Saṅgha of nuns and the laymen the other. … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.11"
msgid "Yeneva bhagavā tenevāhaṃ assaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.12"
msgid "Evaṃ pasannaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.13"
msgid "Idha, bhante, kocideva dhammo samuppādo uppajjeyya, ekato assa bhagavā ekato bhikkhusaṅgho bhikkhunisaṅgho upāsakā upāsikāyo ca. "
msgstr "The Buddha might take one side, and the Saṅgha of monks and the Saṅgha of nuns and the laymen and the laywomen the other. … "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.14"
msgid "Yeneva bhagavā tenevāhaṃ assaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.15"
msgid "Evaṃ pasannaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.16"
msgid "Idha, bhante, kocideva dhammo samuppādo uppajjeyya, ekato assa bhagavā ekato bhikkhusaṅgho bhikkhunisaṅgho upāsakā upāsikāyo sadevako ca loko samārako sabrahmako sassamaṇabrāhmaṇī pajā sadevamanussā. "
msgstr "The Buddha might take one side, and the Saṅgha of monks and the Saṅgha of nuns and the laymen and the laywomen and the world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—the other. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.17"
msgid "Yeneva bhagavā tenevāhaṃ assaṃ. "
msgstr "I’d side with the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn55.23:8.18"
msgid "Evaṃ pasannaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretū”ti. "
msgstr "May the Buddha remember me as having such confidence.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.23:8.19"
msgid "“Evaṃvādī tvaṃ, godhe, mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ kiṃ vadesī”ti? "
msgstr "“Godhā, what do you have to say to Mahānāma when he speaks like this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.23:8.20"
msgid "“Evaṃvādāhaṃ, bhante, mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ na kiñci vadāmi, aññatra kalyāṇā aññatra kusalā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, I have nothing to say to Mahānāma when he speaks like this, except what is good and wholesome.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.23:8.21"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

